stages.name: Collapse
stages.description: The enemy's vanguard has appeared to your three o'clock. Deploy melee Operators to stop them.

stages.name: Protection
stages.description: The enemy has sent more troops. Please make sure you have at least 1 Medic Operator in the squad for healing.

stages.name: Pursuit
stages.description: Enemy unmanned drones have entered the battlefield. Please deploy your Sniper Operators to deal with them.

stages.name: Brawl
stages.description: More enemy drones have entered the battlefield. Please make sure your Sniper Operators are in a position to deal with them.

stages.name: Corruption
stages.description: Enemy hounds are extremely fast and can easily slip through our defenses early on. Please deploy a Vanguard Operator to stop them.

stages.name: Assault
stages.description: The path at the bottom of the battlefield has been opened. Please deploy multiple Vanguard Operators to stop the hounds.

stages.name: Infection
stages.description: Enemy units equipped with shields have high physical defense. Please deploy Caster Operators to defeat them.

stages.name: Hunting
stages.description: Swarms of Originium Slugs are approaching from 9 o'clock. It's recommended to deploy AoE Caster Operators.

stages.name: Nearl
stages.description: More enemy Originium Slugs and shielded soldiers have arrived on the battlefield. Use a combination of Defender Operators and AoE Caster Operators to suppress them.

stages.name: Dilemma
stages.description: Enemy Junkmen have high HP and ATK. Please deploy Defender Operators to block them, and deploy high-damage Operators to defeat them.

stages.name: Blockade Running
stages.description: Mixed enemy troops are coming from the west. Please make good use of the tactics you just learned, and assemble a suitable squad to deal with them.

stages.name: Isolated Island
stages.description:
The battlefield is narrower than before, and the enemies have gotten stronger.
Please make sure your Operators have been upgraded before entering the battlefield.

stages.name: Sprawl
stages.description:
At the same time, members of the Op Reserve Team have run into new enemies on their way to help... Please pay attention to the surprise attack from the north.
<@lv.item><Fixed Squad></> Unable to edit the squad

stages.name: Running Wild
stages.description:
This battlefield is wider and enemies will attack from two paths.
Please note that enemies coming from the southern path have higher defense. Think carefully about where to deploy your Operators.

stages.name: Omen
stages.description: The battlefield is even wider this time. You will need at least 3 melee Operators to block all the enemies.

stages.name: Paralysis
stages.description: This battle takes place on Chernobog's main street. Please have at least 4 melee Operators in the squad to block all the enemies.

stages.name: Catastrophe
stages.description:
Roadblocks help us control enemy movements when they approach from multiple directions. 
Please deploy Roadblocks to control the flow of battle. 
<@lv.item><Roadblock></> Deploy to block a tile on the map. Enemies will attack it if no path is available.

stages.name: The Tyrant
stages.description:
Please combine your Operators' firepower with the Stun Generator on the battlefield to stop the enemy attack.
<@lv.item><Stun Generator></> Pay a cost to activate it, damaging and stunning nearby enemies.

stages.name: Resolve
stages.description:
Be careful of the large number of approaching enemies, but keep an eye on the agile Reunion leader.
The Stun Generator can stop her movement for a short time.
<@lv.item><Stun Generator></> Pay a cost to activate it, damaging and stunning nearby enemies.

stages.name: Rout
stages.description:
Enemies won't slow down their attack even during a Catastrophe.
Please pay attention to enemy ranged units and protect your own ranged Operators.

stages.name: Remnants
stages.description:
We are not far from the outskirts of Chernobog. Hang in there and victory will be ours.
Please pay attention to enemy ranged units and protect your own ranged Operators.

stages.name: The Forgotten
stages.description:
At the same time, Op Reserve Team members have run into W, one of the enemy's leaders, on their way to help... Observe W's movements carefully while defending against the enemy attack.
<@lv.item><Fixed Squad></> Unable to edit the squad

stages.name: Pyrrhic Victory
stages.description:
W's troops have launched their attack from Chernobog's labyrinthine streets. Make good use of the environment.
<@lv.item><Stun Generator></> Pay a cost to activate it, damaging and stunning nearby enemies.

stages.name: To Lungmen
stages.description: The paths on the battlefield are tortuous. Consider using Supporter Operators to suppress the enemy's elite units.

stages.name: Slow-1
stages.description: Please pay attention to the enemy's shielded soldiers, who have high defense.

stages.name: War of Words
stages.description: More enemies with high defense have appeared in the center of the battlefield. Supporter and Caster Operators can reduce their combat power significantly.

stages.name: Slow-2
stages.description: Please pay attention to the aerial units to the north and south.

stages.name: Blockade-1
stages.description:
Deploy Roadblocks in the right places to stop enemies advancing from two directions.
<@lv.item><Roadblock></> Deploy it to block the enemy's advance

stages.name: Blockade-2
stages.description:
The battlefield is even more complicated now. Think carefully before deploying the Roadblocks.
<@lv.item><Roadblock></> Deploy it to block the enemy's advance

stages.name: Presumption of Innocence
stages.description:
Enemies are coming from too many directions this time, complicating your deployment.
Use Roadblocks to control the enemy's advance.
<@lv.item><Roadblock></> Deploy it to block the enemy's advance.

stages.name: Penguin Logistics
stages.description:
Enemy Elite Casters confirmed.
This type of enemy can pose a huge threat to your Operators. Scatter them.

stages.name: Caster-1
stages.description: The enemy's Elite Casters have scattered. Protocol advises taking them out one by one with Sniper Operators.

stages.name: Caster-2
stages.description: The enemy's Elite Casters remain the biggest threat. Scatter your Operators to reduce damage taken.

stages.name: Caster-3
stages.description: The enemy has sent even more Elite Casters. Scatter the Operators as previous.

stages.name: Falling Objects
stages.description:
Massive deployment of enemy Elite Casters confirmed.
Protocol advises destroying them one by one.

stages.name: Hold on Tight
stages.description:
The roof is wide enough to deploy a variety of formations.
Still, watch out for surprise attacks...

stages.name: A Matter of Public Health
stages.description: Enemy's new aerial units have been confirmed on your 1 o'clock and 7 o'clock. Please exercise caution.

stages.name: Trap-1
stages.description: The roof is not surrounded by railings. Make good use of that and things will be much easier.

stages.name: Trap-2
stages.description: Enemies have become stronger. Using the terrain is still the key to victory.

stages.name: No Promises
stages.description:
Some vantage points on the roof are ideal for sniping the enemy's aerial units.
Also, the roof is not surrounded by railings. Can we use that to our advantage...?
<@lv.item><Anti-Air Rune></> Operators deployed on it will attack a bit more slowly but their ATK against aerial units will be increased significantly

stages.name: Cubiculum Obscurum
stages.description:
The battlefield is narrow this time. Please make sure you have enough melee Operators to stop enemies.
<@lv.item><Anti-Air Rune></> Operators deployed on it will attack a bit more slowly but their ATK against aerial units will be increased significantly

stages.name: Suffocation-1
stages.description: Please pay attention to the surprise attack from the south.

stages.name: Suffocation-2
stages.description: The battlefield is completely divided again. Try to defend against enemies from both directions.

stages.name: Suffocation-3
stages.description: Please pay attention to the surprise attack launched by enemy aerial units from the east and west.

stages.name: Beyond Cure
stages.description:
Skullshatterer attacks with her troops! This complicated battlefield will be a test of your skills.
<@lv.item><Medical Rune></> Operators deployed on it are healed over time.

stages.name: Meeting
stages.description:
When fighting in the wild, Operators can take cover in some forms of terrain to reduce damage taken, but please pay attention to the enemy's invisible troops.
<@lv.item><Bush></> Operators deployed on it will not be targeted by enemy ranged attacks.

stages.name: Memory
stages.description:
The enemy has sent even more ranged units.
Eliminate them first as they pose a greater threat.
<@lv.item><Bush></> Operators deployed on it will not be targeted by enemy ranged attacks.

stages.name: Convolution
stages.description:
Enemies equipped with a Detector can disable the effect of Bushes.
Be aware of the enemy leader, who has the ability to disrupt our formation.
<@lv.item><Bush></> Operators deployed on it will not be targeted by enemy ranged attacks.

stages.name: Crack
stages.description:
An previously unknown enemy leader and an elite team are launching a ferocious attack from 6 o'clock.
Deploy operators to engage immediately!
<@lv.item><Bush></> Operators deployed on it will not be targeted by enemy ranged attacks.

stages.name: Call
stages.description:
Enemy's Invisible Casters have been confirmed on the battlefield.
Eliminate them first as they pose a greater threat.
<@lv.item><Bush></> Operators deployed on it will not be targeted by enemy ranged attacks.

stages.name: Decision
stages.description:
The enemy has deployed many invisible ranged units.
Use the Detector to launch a counterattack.
<@lv.item><Detector></> Once activated, it will reveal nearby invisible enemies for a period of time.

stages.name: Roar
stages.description:
The battlefield is complicated. Use Roadblocks to guide enemies into range of our Snipers.
<@lv.item><Roadblock></> Deploy it to block the enemy's advance
<@lv.item><Detector></> Once activated, it will reveal nearby invisible enemies for a period of time.

stages.name: Dusk
stages.description:
Skullshatterer is coming at us with her troops again, only more dangerous...
<@lv.item><Defensive Rune></> Operators deployed on it will have higher DEF

stages.name: Lurking-1
stages.description: Please pay attention to the joint attack of enemy's invisible units and Casters.

stages.name: Lurking-2
stages.description: Enemy only focuses their attack on one spot, but still it's recommended to deploy Operators in the rear.

stages.name: Recon-1
stages.description:
Making good use of the Bushes and the Detector is the key to victory.
<@lv.item><Bush></> Operators deployed on it will not be targeted by enemy's ranged attack
<@lv.item><Detector></> Once activated, it will disable the invisibility of nearby enemies for a certain period

stages.name: Recon-2
stages.description:
Enemies are attacking from different routes this time. Please make sure you have enough melee Operators to stop them.
<@lv.item><Bush></> Operators deployed on it will not be targeted by enemy's ranged attack

stages.name: Recon-3
stages.description: The route is simple this time. It will be a test for your Operators' strength.

stages.name: Ignition-1
stages.description: This battle requires us to concentrate our firepower upon swarms of enemies.

stages.name: Concealed-1
stages.description: A large number of invisible enemies have surrounded the battlefield. Prepare to face them with a solid frontline and far-sighted scouts.

stages.name: Consolation
stages.description: Melee soldiers of another race have been confirmed in Chernobog. Please be careful.

stages.name: A Walk in the Rain
stages.description:
Ranged soldiers of another race have joined the battle.
Protocol advises deploying physical Operators to counter them.

stages.name: Artificial Cold
stages.description:
High-energy Originium radiation has been detected in Chernobog.
If enemy units absorb this radiation...
<@lv.item><Active Originium></>Operators deployed on it and enemies who have passed it will take constant damage, but their ATK and Attack Speed will be increased significantly.

stages.name: Nerves of Steel
stages.description:
The enemy has launched their final attack and approaches from all directions! Deploy Operators to repel them immediately.
<@lv.item><Roadblock></>Deploy it to block the enemy's advance.
<@lv.item><Active Originium></>Operators deployed on it and enemies who have passed it will take constant damage, but their ATK and Attack Speed will be increased significantly.

stages.name: Bureaucracy
stages.description: Enemy melee Arts units have been confirmed on the battlefield. Avoid engaging in melee combat with them. Stay alert.

stages.name: Ignorance
stages.description:
Unknown creatures infected with Oripathy have been found on the battlefield. They deal massive damage to nearby Operators when they die.
In addition, please look out for Heated Paths. They emit burning gas.
<@lv.item><Heated Path></> Deals massive damage to Operators and enemies on it at intervals.

stages.name: Mutual Benefits
stages.description:
A large number of creatures infected with Oripathy have appeared on the battlefield!
Think carefully about when to destroy them.
<@lv.item><Heated Path></> Deals massive damage to Operators and enemies on it at intervals.

stages.name: Acute Stress Disorder
stages.description: A force of mixed enemy troops advances on us from the east. Prepare to engage.

stages.name: Bad to the Bone
stages.description:
Enemy Elite Casters of another race have been confirmed on the battlefield.
They seem to have special powers. Please be careful.
<@lv.item><Heated Path></> Deals massive damage to Operators and enemies on it at intervals.

stages.name: Extinguished Flames
stages.description:
FrostNova and her elite team have the area completely surrounded.
All we can do now is to engage and hold them at our perimeter.

stages.name: Cycle of Enmity
stages.description: Enemy units have been spotted in the wilds outside Lungmen. Beware of the swift moving Breakers and well-protected Spec Ops Casters in particular.

stages.name: Inexpressible
stages.description: A large number of Reunion forces have been spotted in urbanized areas of Lungmen. Beware of Breakers approaching from 12 o'clock.

stages.name: Courage and Mortality
stages.description: Enemy Spec Ops Caster Leaders have spread throughout the battlefield. They can break our operators in an instant without proper preparation against their Arts attacks. Plan carefully.

stages.name: Nobody's Home
stages.description: A swarm of enemy drones approaches from 4 directions. Beware of a new type of enemy drone, the bomb-carrying Bombtails.

stages.name: Unending War
stages.description: An enhanced version of the enemy Bombtail drone has entered the battle. Their AOE damaging explosive bombs can make quick work of our defensive line. Do what you can to counter them beforehand.

stages.name: Surprise Attack
stages.description:
The enemy's Arts Master drones are highly maneuverable and capable of launching Arts attacks from above. Counter them with our newly developed Drone Jammer. 
<@lv.item><Jammer></> can stop nearby enemy drones from firing, greatly reduce their speed, and prevent them from activating special abilities after being deployed.

stages.name: In Life and in Death
stages.description:
Frost Drones greatly reduce the Attack Speed of our nearby units. Counter them with operators or Jammers to prevent them from using their abilities. 
<@lv.item><Jammer></> can stop nearby enemy drones from firing, greatly reduce their speed, and prevent them from activating special abilities after being deployed.

stages.name: Intimate Knowledge
stages.description:
A group of strange enemy soldiers with regeneration abilities have arrived on the battlefield. Eliminate them as quickly as possible. Arrange your deployment to avoid enemy Turrets. 
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical damage to our units.

stages.name: The Devil
stages.description:
Things just keep getting stranger... Enemy Veteran Junkmen now have regenerative abilities as well. Take care to eliminate them as quickly as possible. 
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical damage to our units.

stages.name: The Dark Before Dawn
stages.description:
We are now deep behind enemy lines and there is no going back. Use your tactical expertise and find a way through the crossfire between Mephisto and Faust! 
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical damage to our units.

stages.name: Deadlock
stages.description: Heavily-armored Infected hosts have appeared in Lungmen's urban districts. Not only are they able to shrug off most blows, but they are also capable of regenerating. Exercise caution when dealing with them.

stages.name: Misunderstandings
stages.description: What kind of abominations are those?! New, grotesque Infected combatants have been seen throughout the combat zones of Lungmen. Their speed and power greatly exceed that of regular hosts, so please be careful!

stages.name: Lost at Once
stages.description: The ranks of these aggressive hosts continue to grow, and they will soon apply heavy pressure to our formation. However, their lives seem to also be quickly burning out...

stages.name: Festering Scars
stages.description: This area is under attack by aggressive hosts that hurl projectiles at us. Please beware of their long-range attacks.

stages.name: Who to Kill?
stages.description: A large number of both melee and ranged Possessed Soldiers have appeared. Perhaps a well-planned defense can halt their onslaught...

stages.name: Broken Strings
stages.description:
As the commander of Rhodes Island, you must direct your Operators in a battle against Faust, one of the leaders of Reunion. Be careful.
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical damage to our units.

stages.name: It Fell From the Sky!
stages.description: The legendary Yeti Squadron, an elite anti-Ursus squad of Infected, has appeared in a Chernobog sub-city. Their fighting style is unlike any Reunion forces we've encountered before, so make sure not to underestimate them.

stages.name: Different Perspective
stages.description: The Yeti Squadron, in addition to fielding casters that specialize in ice-based Arts, has also released Originium Slugs that explode in a shower of rime upon death. Please exercise caution.

stages.name: Bells of Liberation
stages.description: The icecleavers, a special group of combatants of the Yeti Squadron, deal massive damage to frozen Operators. Stay calm when fighting them.

stages.name: 'Times Like These'
stages.description: A large number of Yeti Squadron troops have launched an offensive against us, and an arduous battle looms ahead. Make good use of our Operators' various strengths and aim to defeat the enemy.

stages.name: Snow Upon the Tundra
stages.description:
The Yeti Squadron has placed special Originium facilities around the battlefield. Please be prepared to respond accordingly. 
<@lv.item><Originium Ice Crystal></>Periodically releases a frigid wave that will inflict Cold to affected allied units.

stages.name: Frost Upon the Tundra
stages.description:
The 'Oneiros' drones controlled by the Yeti Squadron are capable of inflicting Arts damage in an area upon our Operators, as well as inflicting the Cold status. Please prioritize taking them down.
<@lv.item><Originium Ice Crystal></>Periodically releases a frigid wave that will inflict Cold to affected allied units.

stages.name: Nostalgia
stages.description: Enemy icecleavers have been spotted in conjunction with Oneiros drones. As this will surely be a very difficult battle, please plan carefully to deal with various status abnormalities and enemy attacks.

stages.name: Black Rabbit, White Rabbit
stages.description:
Before us stands the commander of the Yeti Squadron, FrostNova, enhanced with a terrifying power we've never seen before. As she is one of the strongest warriors in Reunion, we must utilize every bit of our strength to overcome her.
<@lv.item><Originium Ice Crystal></> Periodically releases a frigid wave that will inflict Cold to affected allied units.

stages.name: Night of Farewells
stages.description: Remnants of Reunion's forces remain entrenched in the streets of Lungmen, desperately resisting to the bitter end. Prepare for combat.

stages.name: Renegade Blade
stages.description: Mephisto's Herd is no longer under the control of its leader, but their bottomless aggression has prompted them to attack Rhodes Island's ship. Put them out of their misery.

stages.name: Side by Side-1
stages.description: The spearhead of Reunion's reconnaissance force has appeared at the location where we established a concealed facility. Be careful, these are no ordinary Reunion grunts that we're dealing with.

stages.name: Side by Side-2
stages.description: Various Reunion members patrol the passages of the hub layer in the heart of Chernobog. Don't take them lightly; their uniforms... are the same as the Infected guerillas that once fought in the northern tundra of Ursus.

stages.name: Forgotten Lands
stages.description: We've encountered guerilla messengers on our way to the central area of the core city. They employ a unique method of communication and commanding, and we may perhaps be able to draw some inspiration from fighting against them...

stages.name: Fury of the Silent-1
stages.description:
We've found a strange Sarkaz Originium altar in the hub layer... The altar seems to have a strange effect upon the surrounding environment, but we can also leverage it to mount a defense against the enemy.
<@lv.item><Originium Altar></>Periodically emits Pulse Waves to the surrounding tiles, damaging both allied and enemy units.

stages.name: Fury of the Silent-2
stages.description:
Our enemies are no longer fighting in the characteristic style of scattered guerillas. Now is a head-on clash between tactics. Formulate your combat strategy appropriately, and deal a critical blow to the enemy.
<@lv.item><Originium Altar></>Periodically emits Pulse Waves to the surrounding tiles, damaging both allied and enemy units.

stages.name: Flames of the Faint
stages.description:
Sarkaz warriors have entered the battlefield, but be wary - they don't seem to be from the same faction as the guerillas. They even seem to draw inspiration from the Originium altars...?!
<@lv.item><Originium Altar></>Periodically emits Pulse Waves to the surrounding tiles, damaging both allied and enemy units.

stages.name: Stained-1
stages.description:
Sarkaz Casters have appeared on the battlefield, and it seems like the Originium Altars may be affecting their Arts. However, don't panic - we have ways of dealing with them.
<@lv.item><Originium Altar></>Periodically emits Pulse Waves to the surrounding tiles, damaging both allied and enemy units.

stages.name: Stained-2
stages.description:
As Reunion's elite warriors, the Sarkaz Mercenaries have shown formidable strength. Only by defeating them can we continue forward.
<@lv.item><Originium Altar></> Periodically emits Pulse Waves to the surrounding tiles, damaging both allied and enemy units.
<@lv.item><Roadblock></> Deploy to block the enemy's route

stages.name: Aegis of the Infected-1
stages.description: The horn has been sounded. Face the legendary guerillas of Ursus, and turn their own tactics against them! However, those heavily-armored guerilla warriors are indeed the most terrifying combatants of the Ursus army...

stages.name: Guerilla-1
stages.description: The mortars used by the guerillas pose a significant threat to us. These weapons taken from Ursus's military arsenal are terrifying incarnations of the very essence of war.

stages.name: Guerilla-2
stages.description: The guerillas' Vertical Strike Squad has withstood harsh trials and brutal wars. They've fought Ursus for more than a decade, and their will is nigh indomitable. We have but a single moment for a chance at victory.

stages.name: Unrivaled
stages.description: Who has witnessed a battle like this before? Who can survive such a battlefield? Even a simple skirmish has struck fear into our hearts. We do not have the ability to defeat them. We must escape to where they cannot see us.

stages.name: Aegis of the Infected-2
stages.description:
We cannot destroy them, so we will do our best not to be destroyed by them. We must achieve a tactical victory. We strive to paralyze their spinal cord and expose the giant's head to us.
<@lv.item><Originium Altar></> Periodically emits Pulse Waves to the surrounding tiles, damaging both allied and enemy units.

stages.name: Death of a Patriot
stages.description:
They are commanded by the 'Aegis' of the Infected. The most ancient bloodline among the warriors of Sarkaz. Ursus's indomitable incarnation of war. The backbone of the Reunion Movement. Yelena's father.
<@lv.item><Originium Altar></> Periodically emits Pulse Waves to the surrounding tiles, damaging both allied and enemy units.
<@lv.item><Interference Mine></>Upon explosion, deals heavy damage to enemies in the surrounding tiles and amplifies the damage they take for 15 seconds.

stages.name: Yesterday, the Chaff Cracked
stages.description:
In the remote tundra, patrol squads, dressed in black beetle-like uniforms, comb through remote villages to hunt down the Infected. 
<@lv.item><Static Roadblock></>Blocks the movement of Ursus Civilians and Talulah, the Fighter; Can be destroyed by your units.

stages.name: Innocent Flesh and Blood
stages.description:
In the tundras of Ursus, every living creature is under suspicion. They may be murderers, thugs, spies, or simply innocents. 
<@lv.item><Static Roadblock></> Can block the movement of Ursus Civilians and Talulah, the Fighter; Can be destroyed by your units. 
<@lv.item><Ursus Civilian></> Life Points will be deducted by 1 when killed by an enemy.

stages.name: Oatstalk, Easily Alight
stages.description:
Righteous anger from witnessing such brutality is justified. Ursus's manglers are well-trained, and their fangs do not cease just because of their victims' emotions. 
<@lv.item><Static Roadblock></> Can block the movement of Ursus Civilians and Talulah, the Fighter; Can be destroyed by your units. 
<@lv.item><Talulah, the Fighter></> Life Points will be deducted by 1 when killed by an enemy.

stages.name: Sparks, Extinguished in a Touch
stages.description:
Sometimes, protecting others is not a goal, but a process. Also, Ursus's crossbowmen also privately believe that killing others is not a goal, but a process. 
<@lv.item><Static Roadblock></> Can block the movement of Ursus Civilians and Talulah, the Fighter; Can be destroyed by your units.
<@lv.item><Ursus Civilian></> Life Points will be deducted by 1 when killed by an enemy.

stages.name: Cold, Only Perceived
stages.description:
The lowest recorded temperatures of the Northwestern Tundras are sometimes not as bone-chilling as the words of certain individuals. 
<@lv.item><Talulah, the Fighter></> Life Points will be deducted by 1 when killed by an enemy.
<@lv.item><FrostNova's Originium Ice Crystal></> Periodically releases a frigid wave that will inflict Cold on affected enemy units.

stages.name: War, Sprawling Without Cease
stages.description:
The mightiest and meekest both share the same tenacity. 
<@lv.item><Talulah, the Fighter></> Life Points will be deducted by 1 when killed by an enemy.
<@lv.item><Patriot's Originium Altar></> Periodically releases gas in the surrounding 4 tiles, inflicting heavy damage to enemies.

stages.name: Baptism by Tractor Fire
stages.description:
Within the Ursus Army, the history of the Artillery Corps is not particularly lengthy. They are more than happy to arm themselves with the newest technology, and have little concern to spare for who their enemies are. 
<@lv.item><Static Roadblock></> Can block the movement of Ursus Civilians and Talulah, the Fighter; Can be destroyed by your units.
<@lv.item><Ursus Civilian></> Life Points will be deducted by 1 when killed by an enemy.

stages.name: The Heart, Fickle and Impermanent
stages.description:
If you wish to prove yourself before a legend, you must first <@lv.sp>approach perfection</>. Only the commoners shall bleed. Only the noble shall face slander. 
<@lv.item><Static Roadblock></> Can block the movement of Ursus Civilians and Talulah, the Fighter; Can be destroyed by your units.
<@lv.item><Talulah, the Fighter></> Life Points will be deducted by 1 when killed by an enemy.

stages.name: Farewell, to Reunite Once More
stages.description: 07:29:28 Though some friends may be willing to share your pain, you should perhaps <@lv.sp>reach out to them</>. And some may never have been your friends in the first place.

stages.name: Reunited, Only to Separate
stages.description:
To lose. 
<@lv.item><Static Roadblock></> Can block the movement of Ursus Civilians and Talulah, the Fighter; Can be destroyed by your units.
<@lv.item><Ursus Civilian></> Life Points will be deducted by 1 when killed by an enemy.

stages.name: Silent Butcher
stages.description:
The Empire of Ursus has lost many elites throughout its many wars, but is always able to cultivate more. Just as an empire should. 
<@lv.item><Roadblock></> Deploy to block the enemy's route.
<@lv.item><Ursus Civilian></> Life Points will be deducted by 1 when killed by an enemy.

stages.name: Malediction, Bound for Retribution
stages.description: She has not yet died, but she has already seen too much death.

stages.name: Snowfall, Blackening the Earth
stages.description:
Yet, they do not regard anyone as an 'enemy.' The dead and the incompetent have never been among their ranks.
<@lv.item><Static Roadblock></> Can block the movement of Ursus Civilians and Talulah, the Fighter; Can be destroyed by your units.
<@lv.item><Talulah, the Fighter></> Life Points will be deducted by 1 when killed by an enemy.

stages.name: Awakening, a Dream's End
stages.description: An origin, a purpose, a fate, a demise. A tragedy that claims the Herd, all of them. Who can truly <@lv.sp>choose</> their own life?

stages.name: Behold, the Twilight Comes
stages.description:
Memory and reality have both been completely released, and she knows her time has come. 
(Part of this story cannot be skipped the first time you experience it.)
<@lv.item><Heated Path></>Periodically deals great damage to any units on it.

stages.name: Arise, Treading Through Flames
stages.description:
06:26:33 <@lv.sp>Split flame with sword</>, defeat the past with the present, and confront the chaotic with one's self. Rage, and know no compromise. Rage, and keep no silence. 
<@lv.item><Energy Aggregate></>Releases fireballs in the four cardinal directions, dealing Arts damage and inflicting [Burning Breath] (Deals increasing True damage each second, but can be resisted)

stages.name: Cluster-1
stages.description:
Make good use of the Active Originium in the middle of the battlefield and things will be much easier.
<@lv.item><Active Originium></>Operators deployed on it and enemies who have passed it will take constant damage, but their ATK and Attack Speed will be increased significantly

stages.name: Cluster-2
stages.description:
Enemies are coming from more directions. Still it's recommended to build your defense around the Active Originium.
<@lv.item><Active Originium></>Operators deployed on it and enemies who have passed it will take constant damage, but their ATK and Attack Speed will be increased significantly

stages.name: Cluster-3
stages.description:
The alien force has split into two. It may be a good choice to consume their HP by the Active Originium.
<@lv.item><Active Originium></>Operators deployed on it and enemies who have passed it will take constant damage, but their ATK and Attack Speed will be increased significantly

stages.name: Myriapoda-1
stages.description: Please be careful of the Originium Slugs in the south and the north and don't let them go through our defense.

stages.name: Myriapoda-2
stages.description: The battlefield is narrow this time. Please think carefully about where to deploy Operators.

stages.name: Myriapoda-3
stages.description: The battlefield is even narrower. It's recommended to upgrade Operators to get through it.

stages.name: Rage-1
stages.description: Please pay attention to the joint attack of enemy's Originium Slugs and alien elite Casters.

stages.name: Rage-2
stages.description: Scatter the Operators and use ranged Operators to take out the Originium Slugs from afar.

stages.name: Rage-3
stages.description: There is not much space for melee Operators this time. Try using Specialist Operators to cope with the tough enemies on the left.

stages.name: Stand Firm-1
stages.description: A large number of elite enemies have appeared. Please be careful.

stages.name: Entrenched-1
stages.description: The enemies continue their massed assault. Beware of the Wraiths sneaking in from above.

stages.name: Entrenched-2
stages.description: The situation in the field is getting more complicated. Carefully deploy melee Operators to stop the swarm of enemy Breakers.

stages.name: Biting Cold-1
stages.description: Well armored Frost Drones are causing havoc with our forces. Counter them with Caster Operators.

stages.name: Biting Cold-2
stages.description:
The enemy force is a mix of Arts Masters and Frost Drones making it increasingly difficult to handle. Make use of Sniper and Caster Operators and don't forget our Jammers! 
<@lv.item><Jammer></> can stop nearby enemy drones from firing, greatly reduce their speed, and prevent them from activating special abilities after being deployed.

stages.name: Panic-1
stages.description:
Possessed Soldier Leaders can regenerate faster and pose a serious threat. Take them out first. 
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical damage to our units.

stages.name: Panic-2
stages.description:
Defense Crushers are enemy elite units specialized in defense. Their attacks can also stun our melee units. Take advantage of their slow moving speed to counter them. 
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical damage to our units.

stages.name: Hover-1
stages.description:
A large number of unmanned enemy drones have appeared on this operation. Please take charge of the anti-air defense.
<@lv.item><Jammer></> Stops nearby enemy drones from firing, greatly reduces their speed, and prevents them from activating special abilities.

stages.name: Hover-2
stages.description: Enemies attack from different directions in this battle. Be careful of the large number of Casters that are approaching.

stages.name: Abnormality-1
stages.description: A number of possessed enemies have appeared during this battle. Please make sure to fortify your defenses.

stages.name: Condensation-1
stages.description: The Yeti Squadron is utilizing Infused Glacial Originium Slugs in their assault upon us. Please be careful of these aberrant creatures.

stages.name: Condensation-2
stages.description: A failure to handle the synergy between Infused Glacial Originium Slugs and Icecleavers will result in massive losses.

stages.name: Hoarfrost-1
stages.description: An attack from a large number of Infused Glacial Originium Slugs, followed by a wave of Icecleavers, will inflict catastrophic damage to insufficiently prepared squads.

stages.name: Hoarfrost-2
stages.description:
Surrounded by a harsh environment filled with Originium Ice Crystals and powerful Icecleavers, how are we to mount a response to this attack? 
<@lv.item><Originium Ice Crystal></>Periodically releases a frigid wave that will inflict Cold to affected allied units.

stages.name: Ambush-1
stages.description:
Make good use of neural interference landmines to deal with guerillas that are difficult to injure through normal means.
<@lv.item><Interference Mine></>Upon explosion, deals heavy damage to enemies in the surrounding tiles and amplifies the damage they take for 15 seconds.

stages.name: Ambush-2
stages.description:
Use interference mines to establish a defensive line, expand our advantages, and accomplish our strategic goals.
<@lv.item><Interference Mine></>Upon explosion, deals heavy damage to enemies in the surrounding tiles and amplifies the damage they take for 15 seconds.
